641â†’/**
642â†’ * Replace file content in v2 metadata (content update).
643â†’ *
644â†’ * THIS IS THE PRIMARY BENEFIT OF PER-FILE IPNS: content updates publish
645â†’ * ONLY the file's IPNS record. The folder metadata is NOT touched because
646â†’ * the FilePointer still points to the same fileMetaIpnsName, which now
647â†’ * resolves to the updated content.
648â†’ *
649â†’ * @param params.fileId - ID of file to update
650â†’ * @param params.fileIpnsRecord - Updated file IPNS record from updateFileMetadata
651â†’ * @param params.parentFolderState - Parent folder (used only to find the FilePointer)
652â†’ * @returns Void -- no folder metadata update needed
653â†’ * @throws Error if file not found
